1
00:00:32,193 --> 00:00:33,461
(This drama is a work of fiction.)

2
00:00:33,461 --> 00:00:34,696
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

3
00:00:34,696 --> 00:00:35,930
(This drama complied
with production guidelines...)

4
00:00:35,930 --> 00:00:37,165
(for filming child actors and animals.)

5
00:00:41,396 --> 00:00:42,497
Darn it.

6
00:00:44,418 --> 00:00:45,853
Where did those two run off to this time?

7
00:01:04,258 --> 00:01:05,392
Are you kidding me?

8
00:01:06,928 --> 00:01:08,363
Seo Anna...

9
00:01:21,943 --> 00:01:28,916
(Episode 3 Timing)

10
00:01:30,918 --> 00:01:33,721
(Parang-ri diver Jo Mi Hyun)

11
00:01:42,464 --> 00:01:44,733
This will help prevent fogging underwater.

12
00:01:47,002 --> 00:01:48,837
So you're coating them?

13
00:01:49,571 --> 00:01:52,074
The sea has its own clock.

14
00:01:53,675 --> 00:01:55,277
High tide, low tide, and the tidal cycle.

15
00:01:56,044 --> 00:01:57,145
I know that much.

16
00:01:57,446 --> 00:01:58,814
You knew that,

17
00:01:58,814 --> 00:02:00,549
but you went diving
when it was the most dangerous?

18
00:02:02,885 --> 00:02:03,819
Did I?

19
00:02:05,554 --> 00:02:06,822
You got swept away...

20
00:02:07,523 --> 00:02:08,991
because the current was too strong.

21
00:02:17,866 --> 00:02:19,868
The time when the current is weakest,

22
00:02:19,868 --> 00:02:22,337
between low tide and high tide,
is called slack tide.

23
00:02:23,205 --> 00:02:24,540
It's the only time...

24
00:02:24,907 --> 00:02:27,242
the sea allows divers into the water,
twice a day.

25
00:02:28,577 --> 00:02:30,612
And when's that?

26
00:02:32,447 --> 00:02:33,415
Right now.

27
00:02:38,954 --> 00:02:39,922
I see.

28
00:02:40,155 --> 00:02:43,192
It does look a bit calm.

29
00:02:44,493 --> 00:02:45,494
Let's hurry.

30
00:02:47,229 --> 00:02:49,565
The slack tide only lasts
up to three hours.

31
00:02:57,840 --> 00:02:58,941
Wait for me!

32
00:03:02,177 --> 00:03:03,212
Wait.

33
00:03:04,012 --> 00:03:05,280
I told you to wait for me!

34
00:03:35,777 --> 00:03:37,246
Will you stand up? You're heavy.

35
00:03:41,316 --> 00:03:42,384
You didn't have to say that...

36
00:03:45,087 --> 00:03:47,389
Hey, you jerks!

37
00:03:51,493 --> 00:03:52,394
Baek Su Jeong?

38
00:03:53,929 --> 00:03:54,863
Seo Anna.

39
00:03:55,130 --> 00:03:56,331
I was a fool...

40
00:03:57,766 --> 00:03:59,134
for trusting you.

41
00:04:00,669 --> 00:04:02,337
You bitch!

42
00:04:02,337 --> 00:04:04,206
Hey, you're going to fall!

43
00:04:07,676 --> 00:04:09,878
Stop pretending to be all nice!

44
00:04:10,679 --> 00:04:11,980
What are you talking about?

45
00:04:11,980 --> 00:04:14,149
You said you're not interested
in Deok Hyun!

46
00:04:14,149 --> 00:04:16,752
How could you do this to me?

47
00:04:16,752 --> 00:04:18,420
I told you! I'm not!

48
00:04:18,420 --> 00:04:20,722
You said you didn't think
he was sexy at all!

49
00:04:20,989 --> 00:04:22,024
Sexy?

50
00:04:22,024 --> 00:04:23,258
Him? "Sexy"?

51
00:04:23,258 --> 00:04:24,159
Hey!

52
00:04:38,841 --> 00:04:39,775
Deok Hyun.

53
00:04:40,042 --> 00:04:41,176
Me first.

54
00:04:41,677 --> 00:04:43,478
I got hurt more than her.

55
00:04:46,882 --> 00:04:48,383
Take care of it by yourselves.

56
00:04:50,185 --> 00:04:51,520
Where are you going?

57
00:04:51,820 --> 00:04:53,488
I'm hurting over here.

58
00:04:53,488 --> 00:04:55,490
You should patch me up!

59
00:04:55,490 --> 00:04:56,825
Deok Hyun!

60
00:04:57,092 --> 00:04:58,193
Hey!

61
00:04:58,193 --> 00:04:59,461
I'll do it for you. Hang on.

62
00:05:01,263 --> 00:05:02,264
Come here.

63
00:05:06,134 --> 00:05:07,536
Stay still.

64
00:05:09,505 --> 00:05:12,241
You think this will make me forgive you?

65
00:05:13,509 --> 00:05:16,078
It's not what you think.

66
00:05:16,478 --> 00:05:17,613
Don't lie to me.

67
00:05:18,013 --> 00:05:19,781
You were diving together,

68
00:05:19,781 --> 00:05:22,284
eating together,
working out together,

69
00:05:22,584 --> 00:05:24,887
and touching each other...

70
00:05:25,787 --> 00:05:26,655
Hey!

71
00:05:26,989 --> 00:05:28,824
I like men with brighter skin,

72
00:05:28,824 --> 00:05:30,158
and men who are sweet.

73
00:05:30,659 --> 00:05:31,827
That's what I mean.

74
00:05:32,394 --> 00:05:33,595
Deok Hyun...

75
00:05:33,595 --> 00:05:36,465
has a sweet face!

76
00:05:37,799 --> 00:05:39,168
Su Jeong.

77
00:05:42,371 --> 00:05:43,305
You and I...

78
00:05:43,906 --> 00:05:44,907
are no longer besties.

79
00:05:45,607 --> 00:05:47,709
This is war, you traitor.

80
00:05:48,210 --> 00:05:51,513
Don't ever call me by my first name again.

81
00:05:52,147 --> 00:05:53,982
Seo Anna!

82
00:05:59,154 --> 00:06:00,956
We weren't even besties
in the first place.

83
00:06:03,025 --> 00:06:04,493
It's been ten years since we met.

84
00:06:27,649 --> 00:06:28,684
Aren't we going diving?

85
00:06:29,484 --> 00:06:30,919
I told you earlier,

86
00:06:31,220 --> 00:06:33,388
the slack tide only lasts
up to three hours.

87
00:06:35,424 --> 00:06:36,291
Plus,

88
00:06:37,292 --> 00:06:39,428
you should keep that wound dry
for a while.

89
00:06:43,432 --> 00:06:44,366
You know,

90
00:06:45,534 --> 00:06:46,902
you're rude,

91
00:06:47,736 --> 00:06:49,071
but you're strangely nice.

92
00:06:50,005 --> 00:06:50,939
That's ridiculous.

93
00:06:56,411 --> 00:06:58,580
Even if we didn't dive,
you should wash and dry that.

94
00:06:59,014 --> 00:07:00,883
Any salt on it can cause corrosion.

95
00:07:02,684 --> 00:07:03,886
Yeah, yeah.

96
00:07:05,621 --> 00:07:06,889
I shouldn't have said anything.

97
00:07:07,956 --> 00:07:10,893
And you should make up with your friend.

98
00:07:12,794 --> 00:07:13,695
Why?

99
00:07:13,695 --> 00:07:15,464
Are you worried rumors will spread...

100
00:07:15,464 --> 00:07:16,999
about you two-timing us?

101
00:07:19,201 --> 00:07:21,436
There's a right timing in relationships,
just like the sea.

102
00:07:22,838 --> 00:07:24,139
Once you miss it,

103
00:07:25,807 --> 00:07:27,476
that timing might not return
for a long time.

104
00:07:32,915 --> 00:07:34,216
I guess I'm meddling.

105
00:07:42,057 --> 00:07:42,991
What was that?

106
00:07:44,193 --> 00:07:45,127
Acting like he's all cool...

107
00:07:50,065 --> 00:07:52,901
(Parang-ri diver Jo Mi Hyun)

108
00:07:52,901 --> 00:07:53,769
Well,

109
00:07:54,203 --> 00:07:55,504
it's true that I pushed aside
everything...

110
00:07:56,338 --> 00:07:57,739
apart from swimming.

111
00:07:58,874 --> 00:08:00,008
(EAT SLEEP SWIM)

112
00:08:00,008 --> 00:08:01,910
Stop sending me food.

113
00:08:02,377 --> 00:08:04,012
I can't even eat it all.

114
00:08:04,713 --> 00:08:06,615
I can take care of myself,

115
00:08:07,115 --> 00:08:08,917
so stop worrying.

116
00:08:10,419 --> 00:08:11,854
I said it's fine!

117
00:08:13,789 --> 00:08:15,424
"I'm busy now, so later."

118
00:08:19,361 --> 00:08:21,129
"I can talk to her next time."

119
00:08:21,864 --> 00:08:22,831
"Later."

120
00:08:42,651 --> 00:08:45,587
That little brat.
How could she not touch any of this?

121
00:08:48,156 --> 00:08:49,725
That's so hurtful.

122
00:08:52,995 --> 00:08:54,496
I kept telling myself "later,"

123
00:08:55,164 --> 00:08:56,131
and in the end...

124
00:08:57,199 --> 00:08:58,367
I hurt her.

125
00:09:14,116 --> 00:09:15,184
I missed...

126
00:09:16,585 --> 00:09:17,586
an important timing.

127
00:09:18,787 --> 00:09:21,690
(Parang-ri diver Jo Mi Hyun)

128
00:09:26,361 --> 00:09:27,296
How am I...

129
00:09:28,564 --> 00:09:30,199
supposed to make up with her?

130
00:10:10,239 --> 00:10:11,273
Are these red beans?

131
00:10:12,307 --> 00:10:13,976
Jeez. I have no idea.

132
00:10:15,043 --> 00:10:17,479
This isn't some supermarket.

133
00:10:18,146 --> 00:10:19,248
There won't be red beans.

134
00:10:19,948 --> 00:10:21,583
Even if there are,
it's not the right season.

135
00:10:25,354 --> 00:10:27,589
Red beans are planted in the summer
and harvested in the fall.

136
00:10:30,692 --> 00:10:31,960
Thanks for the info.

137
00:10:38,133 --> 00:10:38,967
What?

138
00:10:39,234 --> 00:10:40,202
You said there aren't any.

139
00:10:40,502 --> 00:10:42,137
I just said it's not harvest season yet.

140
00:10:42,137 --> 00:10:43,405
These are from last year.

141
00:10:45,741 --> 00:10:46,775
Thank you.

142
00:11:32,354 --> 00:11:33,255
Hey!

143
00:11:34,323 --> 00:11:35,157
Hey!

144
00:11:36,992 --> 00:11:39,728
Help me so I won't miss that timing.

145
00:11:46,335 --> 00:11:47,870
Come on.

146
00:11:53,208 --> 00:11:54,109
Open it.

147
00:12:02,584 --> 00:12:04,453
Stir it like this.

148
00:12:29,378 --> 00:12:30,179
All right.

149
00:12:31,046 --> 00:12:32,948
Keep stirring.

150
00:13:06,481 --> 00:13:07,482
If you think about it,

151
00:13:08,050 --> 00:13:09,384
everything's about timing.

152
00:13:17,893 --> 00:13:18,861
Diving,

153
00:13:19,728 --> 00:13:20,629
relationships,

154
00:13:21,964 --> 00:13:22,898
and even dough.

155
00:13:23,999 --> 00:13:25,334
It's all about timing.

156
00:13:55,397 --> 00:13:56,565
How long do I have to do this?

157
00:13:57,366 --> 00:13:58,600
Bring it here.

158
00:15:04,833 --> 00:15:05,667
Look.

159
00:15:46,808 --> 00:15:48,076
Like how even this honey bread...

160
00:15:48,944 --> 00:15:50,245
requires patience...

161
00:15:51,280 --> 00:15:53,015
and the right moment,

162
00:15:54,183 --> 00:15:56,552
everything has the right timing.

163
00:16:03,192 --> 00:16:04,326
Come on. Try it.

164
00:16:20,776 --> 00:16:22,144
Come to Parang Elementary School.

165
00:16:22,144 --> 00:16:24,112
Right now!

166
00:16:37,259 --> 00:16:40,395
That brat. Why did she make me
come all the way here?

167
00:16:47,336 --> 00:16:48,303
Hey!

168
00:16:55,477 --> 00:16:56,678
Baek Su Jeong. What is it?

169
00:16:57,079 --> 00:16:59,081
You called me here, but you're late.

170
00:17:00,349 --> 00:17:01,283
Here!

171
00:17:01,283 --> 00:17:02,484
Have these on the way to Seoul.

172
00:17:09,658 --> 00:17:10,659
Honey bread?

173
00:17:11,093 --> 00:17:12,528
I'm already sick of this bread,

174
00:17:12,528 --> 00:17:13,929
and you want me to eat it in Seoul too?

175
00:17:14,763 --> 00:17:17,900
You didn't even tell me
you were going to Seoul,

176
00:17:18,901 --> 00:17:21,003
so I didn't have time to prepare a gift.

177
00:17:30,112 --> 00:17:30,979
Seriously?

178
00:17:31,280 --> 00:17:32,981
You think some honey bread
will make us even?

179
00:17:33,815 --> 00:17:35,217
It's not just some honey bread.

180
00:17:35,851 --> 00:17:36,985
You said it yourself...

181
00:17:37,553 --> 00:17:40,656
that honey bread
is a way of wishing someone a safe trip.

182
00:17:47,329 --> 00:17:49,097
You should eat them on the way.

183
00:17:50,732 --> 00:17:53,702
Eating it here or on the way,
it's all the same.

184
00:17:53,702 --> 00:17:54,636
No, it isn't!

185
00:17:54,937 --> 00:17:56,205
My dad told me...

186
00:17:56,471 --> 00:17:59,942
honey bread lasts a long time
because of all the syrup.

187
00:18:00,309 --> 00:18:02,611
That's why Mom
always makes them for Dad...

188
00:18:02,611 --> 00:18:04,479
when he goes out to sea.

189
00:18:06,715 --> 00:18:08,450
It's a way of wishing him a safe trip.

190
00:18:22,998 --> 00:18:24,032
So...

191
00:18:24,399 --> 00:18:25,734
it's not just some honey bread.

192
00:18:26,835 --> 00:18:27,870
It's my greeting.

193
00:18:30,439 --> 00:18:31,406
Thanks to you,

194
00:18:32,641 --> 00:18:33,775
I had a safe trip.

195
00:18:34,443 --> 00:18:35,377
Baek Su Jeong.

196
00:18:37,346 --> 00:18:39,147
Don't be silly.

197
00:18:41,617 --> 00:18:43,719
What? Are you crying?

198
00:18:45,954 --> 00:18:47,055
No, I'm not!

199
00:18:47,489 --> 00:18:48,690
My throat's just dry from eating this.

200
00:18:53,662 --> 00:18:55,631
What? Did you just laugh?

201
00:18:55,831 --> 00:18:57,699
Yeah, I did! So what?

202
00:19:00,435 --> 00:19:01,436
How is it?

203
00:19:01,436 --> 00:19:02,437
Is it good?

204
00:19:02,638 --> 00:19:03,805
It's my first time making them.

205
00:19:07,042 --> 00:19:08,076
They're really...

206
00:19:11,246 --> 00:19:12,181
tasty.

207
00:19:16,051 --> 00:19:18,320
That doesn't mean I'm going
to let you have Deok Hyun.

208
00:19:18,520 --> 00:19:19,922
Don't even think about it.

209
00:19:21,723 --> 00:19:23,125
I told you, I'm not interested!

210
00:19:23,125 --> 00:19:24,193
You'd better not be lying.

211
00:19:26,395 --> 00:19:27,830
- What?
- It's raining.

212
00:19:27,830 --> 00:19:28,664
It's raining!

213
00:19:30,766 --> 00:19:32,668
The weather was so nice, though!

214
00:19:33,368 --> 00:19:34,203
Run!

215
00:19:56,124 --> 00:19:58,293
There's a typhoon coming.
We won't be able to dive for a while.

216
00:19:58,293 --> 00:19:59,127
What?

217
00:20:02,331 --> 00:20:03,499
What are you waiting for? Help me out.

218
00:20:07,236 --> 00:20:08,237
Everything...

219
00:20:08,837 --> 00:20:09,838
has the right timing.

220
00:20:12,641 --> 00:20:15,410
Typhoon Bambi is quickly moving north.

221
00:20:15,777 --> 00:20:19,181
Heavy rain and strong winds
are continuing nationwide,

222
00:20:19,181 --> 00:20:22,651
with downpours exceeding 80mm per hour
along the southern coast,

223
00:20:22,651 --> 00:20:25,821
raising concerns about damage.

224
00:20:26,054 --> 00:20:28,590
The typhoon is expected
to be at its strongest...

225
00:20:28,590 --> 00:20:30,025
between tonight
and early tomorrow morning.

226
00:20:31,793 --> 00:20:32,694
Darn it!

227
00:20:34,463 --> 00:20:35,464
Jeez!

228
00:20:37,399 --> 00:20:39,034
What are you doing? Hurry up.

229
00:20:39,034 --> 00:20:40,369
Just wait, all right?

230
00:20:42,371 --> 00:20:43,605
Hold it properly!

231
00:20:46,975 --> 00:20:47,809
Darn it!

232
00:20:59,354 --> 00:21:00,722
While waiting for the right time,

233
00:21:01,423 --> 00:21:03,058
hardships may come,

234
00:21:03,725 --> 00:21:05,060
and things may fall apart,

235
00:21:14,736 --> 00:21:16,238
but even the roughest typhoon...

236
00:21:17,072 --> 00:21:18,507
passes eventually.

237
00:21:35,324 --> 00:21:36,291
Shall we go today?

238
00:21:40,762 --> 00:21:41,697
Diving.

239
00:22:02,384 --> 00:22:05,420
Just as the sea gives birth to new life...

240
00:22:09,825 --> 00:22:12,160
after the typhoon passes
and washes away the impurities,

241
00:22:17,499 --> 00:22:18,400
the right timing...

242
00:22:19,601 --> 00:22:20,636
arrives.

243
00:22:25,574 --> 00:22:26,475
Let's go.

244
00:22:40,556 --> 00:22:41,657
Wait!

245
00:22:44,393 --> 00:22:45,594
Who dives...

246
00:22:48,463 --> 00:22:49,531
on an empty stomach?

247
00:22:51,400 --> 00:22:53,368
I dive on an empty stomach.

248
00:22:54,002 --> 00:22:56,171
Oh, dear.

249
00:22:56,638 --> 00:23:00,075
Then you can have this for lunch.

250
00:23:01,310 --> 00:23:02,144
What about me?

251
00:23:02,644 --> 00:23:03,745
I can eat right now.

252
00:23:04,813 --> 00:23:06,048
I don't have any...

253
00:23:06,915 --> 00:23:07,916
for you.

254
00:23:13,088 --> 00:23:13,956
You can do it!

255
00:23:45,687 --> 00:23:46,855
Let's dive here.

256
00:23:50,459 --> 00:23:51,827
This is different from swimming.

257
00:23:52,728 --> 00:23:55,030
You have to hold your breath,
not breathe out.

258
00:23:56,899 --> 00:23:58,167
Hold my breath...

259
00:24:00,502 --> 00:24:01,803
Then I'll see you down there.

260
00:25:09,271 --> 00:25:11,206
I can't tell anything apart.

261
00:25:17,880 --> 00:25:19,314
Where did you get that?

262
00:25:20,349 --> 00:25:22,217
You didn't buy that, did you?

263
00:25:22,651 --> 00:25:24,620
Did you forget everything I taught you?

264
00:25:24,620 --> 00:25:26,255
I remember!

265
00:25:26,522 --> 00:25:27,689
But it's easier said than done.

266
00:25:29,324 --> 00:25:30,459
Put on your goggles.

267
00:25:33,562 --> 00:25:34,429
And...

268
00:25:35,397 --> 00:25:36,331
give me your hand.

269
00:25:36,932 --> 00:25:37,766
What?

270
00:25:40,169 --> 00:25:41,837
Take a deep breath.

271
00:26:23,645 --> 00:26:25,914
Once you go underwater,
it'll probably look like this.

272
00:26:26,982 --> 00:26:28,851
That's just a rock.

273
00:26:31,353 --> 00:26:32,254
Do you see these?

274
00:26:35,858 --> 00:26:36,725
Breathing holes?

275
00:26:39,695 --> 00:26:41,697
Rocks don't have holes like this.

276
00:26:42,564 --> 00:26:44,666
When you look closely...

277
00:26:45,133 --> 00:26:46,735
among the rocks underwater,

278
00:26:47,369 --> 00:26:49,137
you'll sense the abalones breathing.

279
00:27:50,599 --> 00:27:51,600
I got it!

280
00:27:52,034 --> 00:27:53,168
I got one!

281
00:27:54,036 --> 00:27:54,870
What?

282
00:27:55,404 --> 00:27:56,505
What did you get?

283
00:27:57,172 --> 00:27:58,173
An abalone!

284
00:28:03,011 --> 00:28:04,179
An abalone!

285
00:28:04,680 --> 00:28:06,682
You really are Parang-ri's mermaid.

286
00:28:06,682 --> 00:28:09,051
Seo Anna, nice!

287
00:28:13,088 --> 00:28:14,056
Look!

288
00:28:21,096 --> 00:28:23,532
Don't get ahead of yourself
just because you got one.

289
00:28:23,532 --> 00:28:24,967
Dive only as long
as you can hold your breath.

290
00:28:25,400 --> 00:28:26,568
Quit nagging.

291
00:28:28,403 --> 00:28:31,406
I've been waiting for this day, you know.

292
00:28:31,840 --> 00:28:32,808
So trust me.

293
00:28:33,842 --> 00:28:34,843
I'll see you underwater.

294
00:30:16,612 --> 00:30:18,347
If I keep waiting for the right moment,

295
00:30:19,615 --> 00:30:20,716
will my dream...

296
00:30:22,351 --> 00:30:23,886
ever shine...

297
00:30:25,587 --> 00:30:26,522
again?

298
00:30:44,506 --> 00:30:45,774
Are you that happy?

299
00:30:46,608 --> 00:30:47,609
Yes.

300
00:30:47,609 --> 00:30:48,510
Thanks to you.

301
00:30:51,113 --> 00:30:52,014
And since I'm in a good mood,

302
00:30:53,549 --> 00:30:55,751
I'll take back what I said about you.

303
00:30:58,487 --> 00:30:59,888
About you being rude...

304
00:31:00,756 --> 00:31:02,457
but strangely nice.

305
00:31:02,991 --> 00:31:03,926
Yes?

306
00:31:05,027 --> 00:31:08,197
You're not rude,
but you're not nice either.

307
00:31:10,465 --> 00:31:12,334
Isn't that worse, then?

308
00:31:13,001 --> 00:31:14,069
But...

309
00:31:14,870 --> 00:31:17,005
you're like the sea.

310
00:31:21,243 --> 00:31:23,679
On the surface, you push others away
like rough waves,

311
00:31:24,513 --> 00:31:26,181
but you're actually deep and quiet inside.

312
00:31:28,083 --> 00:31:29,017
So...

313
00:31:29,985 --> 00:31:31,320
though I haven't known you long,

314
00:31:32,721 --> 00:31:34,189
I feel like I can trust you.

315
00:31:41,296 --> 00:31:42,865
You're a bad judge of character.

316
00:31:44,399 --> 00:31:45,634
I know you feel good.

317
00:31:46,535 --> 00:31:47,469
In any case,

318
00:31:48,203 --> 00:31:49,238
thank you.

319
00:31:53,842 --> 00:31:54,877
For teaching me...

320
00:31:55,644 --> 00:31:56,712
diving.

321
00:32:36,485 --> 00:32:37,286
Hey.

322
00:32:37,819 --> 00:32:38,654
Hey.

323
00:32:42,024 --> 00:32:44,760
I heard this guy lives here. Is it true?

324
00:32:46,361 --> 00:32:47,296
Who?

325
00:32:49,965 --> 00:32:51,466
Oh, him!

326
00:32:51,466 --> 00:32:52,501
Yun Deok Hyun!

327
00:32:53,168 --> 00:32:54,670
That's Yun Deok Hyun!

328
00:32:55,370 --> 00:32:56,338
He lives over there...

329
00:32:57,039 --> 00:32:58,307
in the house with the red roof.

330
00:33:01,210 --> 00:33:03,712
But why...

331
00:33:04,713 --> 00:33:06,148
are you looking for Yun Deok Hyun?

332
00:33:10,786 --> 00:33:11,787
I'm just asking...

333
00:33:12,654 --> 00:33:13,488
Why?

334
00:33:16,124 --> 00:33:17,759
Is he someone I shouldn't be looking for?

335
00:33:19,428 --> 00:33:20,429
No...

336
00:33:21,163 --> 00:33:22,364
It's not that.

337
00:33:27,603 --> 00:33:30,305
I just have a debt to repay him.

338
00:33:30,305 --> 00:33:31,340
No need to be so scared.

339
00:33:35,811 --> 00:33:36,812
Wow!

340
00:33:37,346 --> 00:33:38,547
Living the good life, I see...

341
00:33:40,415 --> 00:33:41,450
Yun Deok Hyun.

342
00:34:16,919 --> 00:34:18,921
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
